This paper focuses on a technique for helping programmers understand and fix bugs in software. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for identifying invariants and classifiers, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper applies the technique to real-world bugs, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY).
